Job Posting Analysis¶

Business Objectives:
Our main business objectives are to understand the dynamics of the labour market of Armenia using the online job portal post.

Business questions answering to our business objectives are defined as follows:
Job Nature and Company Profiles:
What are the types of jobs that are in demand in Armenia? How are the job natures changing over time?
Desired Characteristics and Skill-Sets:
What are the desired characteristics and skill-set of the candidates based on the job description dataset? How these are desired characteristics changing over time?
IT Job Classification:
Build a classifier that can tell us from the job description and company description whether a job is IT or not, so that this column can be automatically populated for new job postings. After doing so, understand what important factors are which drives this classification.
Similarity of Jobs:
Given a job title, find the 5 top jobs that are of a similar nature, based on the job post.
Text Mining Goals:
The text mining goals is a set of sub-goals to answer our business questions: For the IT Job classification business question, you should aim to create supervised learning classification models that are able to classify based on the job text data accurately, is it an IT job.

def outlier_miss_treat(x):
    x = x.clip(upper = x.quantile(0.99))
    x = x.clip(lower = x.quantile(0.01))
    x = x.fillna(x.median())
    return x

data_num = data_num.apply(outlier_miss_treat)

In [35]:
def create_corpus(x):
    corpus = []
    wn = WordNetLemmatizer()
    ps = PorterStemmer()
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(0, x.shape[0])):
        #print(i,end='\r')
        msg = re.sub('[^a-zA-Z]', ' ', x[i])
        msg = msg.lower()
        msg = msg.split()
        #msg = word_tokenize(X_train[i].lower()) #Not preferred as it doesn't handle metachars, numbers
        msg = [wn.lemmatize(word) for word in msg if not word in set(eng_stopwords)] #wn.lemmatize #ps.stem
        #msg = nltk.pos_tag(msg)
        #msg = [item[0] for item in msg if item[1] in pos_tag_list]
        msg = ' '.join(msg)
        corpus.append(msg)
        #break
    return corpus
# Applying cleaning for the columns except It, Year for i in data.columns[:-2]: data[i] = create_corpus(data[i])

def pos_tag(x):
    l = []
    for i in tqdm_notebook(range(0, x.shape[0])):
        msg = x[i]
        msg = msg.split()
        msg = nltk.pos_tag(msg)
        msg = [item[0] for item in msg if item[1] in pos_tag_list]
        msg = ' '.join(msg)
        l.append(msg)
    return l
data['jobpost'] = pos_tag(data['jobpost'])

sd = data[data.Title=='software developer']['jobpost']
freq_words= {}
for d in sd:
    tokens = nltk.wordpunct_tokenize(d)
    for token in tokens:
        if len(token)>=3:
            if token in freq_words:
                count = freq_words[token]
                count = count + 1
                freq_words[token] = count
            else:
                freq_words[token] = 1

In [75]:
def pred_rate(cls, X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test):
    # fitting
    cls.fit(X_train, y_train) 
    # pred
    y_pred_train = cls.predict(X_train)
    y_pred_test = cls.predict(X_test)

    print('cm train\n',confusion_matrix(y_train, y_pred_train))
    print('cm test \n',confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_test))

    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_train, y_pred_train)
    print("\nAccuracy train : {} %".format(round(accuracy*100,3)))
    accuracy = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
    print("Accuracy test  : {} %".format(round(accuracy*100,3)))
    
    train_auc = roc_auc_score(y_train, y_pred_train)
    test_auc  = roc_auc_score(y_test, y_pred_test)
    print("\nAUC Train : ", train_auc)
    print("AUC Test  : ", test_auc)
    
    print('\nClassification Report Train :')
    print(classification_report(y_train, y_pred_train))
    print('\nClassification Report Test :')
    print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_test))
    print('-----------------------------------------------------------')

def print_centroids(cm, num):
    original_space_centroids = svd_k.inverse_transform(cm.cluster_centers_)
    order_centroids = original_space_centroids.argsort()[:, ::-1]
    terms = tv_k.get_feature_names()
    for i in range(num):
        print("Cluster %d:" % i, end='')
        for ind in order_centroids[i, :10]:
            print(' %s' % terms[ind], end='')
        print()

In [83]:
def get_orgs_from_doc(document):
    doc = nlp(document)
    org_entities = ""
    
    for ent in doc.ents:
        stripped_content = ent.text.strip()
        if stripped_content != "" and stripped_content[0] != "-":
            if ent.label_ == "ORG":
                entity = ent.text
                entity = entity.replace("/", " ").replace("\n", " ")
                org_entities += entity + " "
                
    return org_entities
%time qual_ORG = data.RequiredQual.astype(str).apply(get_orgs_from_doc)qual_ORG.to_pickle("qual_ORG.pkl")
